==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mobilize
<hw>Mob"i*lize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Mobilized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Mobilizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>mobiliser</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To assemble and organize
and make ready for use or action; <as>as, to <ex>mobilize</ex>
volunteers for the election campaign</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mobilise, marshal.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <def>To put in a state of
readiness for active service in war, as an army corps; <as>as, to
<ex>mobilize</ex> the National Guard</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mobilise, militarize, militarise.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

